Are your followers dropping off like a bad habit? This could be why...‚Å£
‚Å£
1.  Your followers are confused because your page isn‚Äôt niched specific. You‚Äôre bouncing all over the place from selling hair to selling fruit baskets. ‚Å£

When you post sporadically just to get a sale it‚Äôs like a no good man who only calls you at night for a booty call. ‚Å£

12 Rules for Good Trading

Here are 12 great rules that can give new traders a quick list to see what the right questions to answer that will lead to good trading and also a guide to more experienced traders that just can't get to consistent profitable trading over the long term.

Carry your own and paper:

1. Create your own quantified trading system with an edge that fits your own goals for potential returns and your personal risk tolerance

2. Keep your internal mental dialogue positive using both logic and reason as your thoughts to council yourself in during your trading. Your mind is the battlefield

3. Only be friends with other traders that are positive and helpful in your journey.

4. Only compare yourself with your past performance not other traders. Everyone has their own goals and path. No follow follow

5. Do not do anything that would hurt your confidence in your own discipline. You know yourself, so guard your confidence

6. Do not concern yourself with anyone's trading results but your own. Face your front and Dey your lane.

7. Focus on learning how to build your own trading system and stop jumping from one system to another.

8. Always be honest with yourself about your own knowledge and understanding about trading and the markets. Confidence can only come after competence.

9. Assume you can learn one valuable trading lesson from every trader. Even if it is what
not to do.

10. Be precise in your risk management but flexible in your expectations of outcome. Don‚Äôt expect $1,000 profit monthly 4rm $100 account

11. Encourage new traders to learn the importance of position sizing, entry and exit signals and the right mindset

12. Help new traders when you can share your own experience to shorten their learning
curve. Like I do with my free trade that has been getting my students minimum $200 profit per week

These are the two keys to investing:

1. Investing early makes the most of compound interest. Earning interest on our interest!

2. Investing often, or dollar cost averaging, helps us ride out the ups and downs of the market.

I started investing when I was 21 and invest on a monthly basis! üí∑

In the example in this post, starting at 21 and investing ¬£100 per month can lead to over ¬£500k by the time you‚Äôre 71! ü§ë

Starting early (if you haven‚Äôt started yet, start now!) and investing often are the two keys! üîë

description:
It's Reselling Term Thursday!! Today's word is "Ombre"!! Ombre clothing is that Multicolor fabric that look dip dyed as it transitions from color to color with light to dark transitions! It's a great keyword to use when selling this type of garment online!
.
What Is Ombre?
.
In fashion, the term¬†ombre¬†refers to the graduation of color in a garment.¬†The word usually refers to a garment that is monochromatic but has a graduated variation in the saturation of the color.¬†For example, a green ombre dress may be very pale green at the hem, but the fabric becomes deeper in color the as it reaches from the bottom hem to the shoulder straps at the top of the dress, where the color might be a very deep forest green.
.
There are a number of ways to create ombre fabrics.¬†With current textile technology, it is possible to use numerous threads that range in color saturation or a single spool of thread that has been specifically dyed to create this effect.¬†This kind of effect can also be created by dipping fabric into a vat of dye and very slowly pulling it out.¬†In so doing, the part of the garment that is in the dye for the longest will have the deepest color.¬†The variation will depend on how long each section of the fabric is left to soak in the dye.
.
While ombre fabrics can be used in any kind of garment and many kinds of accessories, it is most common in dresses.¬†Many famous designers, including Alberta Ferretti, Zac Posen, Vivienne Westwood, Badgley Mischka, and Nicole Miller, have featured such dresses in their clothing lines.¬†Some fashion commentators have regarded this effect as the new tie-dye.
.
This kind of coloring in fabric can be either very subtle or quite bold.¬†A scarf that is dyed to go from a light camel color to a dark chocolate brown color, for example, is a rather muted example of how it can be used.
.
From: https://m.wisegeek.com/in-fashion-what-does-ombre-mean.htm

description:
1300 lives changed. In a single MONTH.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
That makes my jaw drop and heart flutter all at once. ‚†Ä
‚†Ä
When I first started coaching, it was because it felt like I‚Äôd stepped into a parallel universe. I was literally watching myself change more and more. Going from someone who was sluggish, self-pitying and pessimistic‚Äî to someone who was excited to start the day, learning to love themselves, and finding joy in the journey. I‚Äôd seen how much I was changing ‚Äî and I knew I couldn‚Äôt be the only one. I couldn‚Äôt be the only‚†Ä
woman who for one reason or another felt stuck and unhappy with who she was. I couldn‚Äôt be the only one capable of changing ‚Äî and I wanted to help other women see  mitheir potential.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
‚ÄúIf I help one woman by doing this - it will all be worth it,‚Äù I thought. And I still lead with that. Each time I hear from one of my clients about how they are proud of the habits they‚Äôre creating, how they are more confident then ever - it makes me want to cry happy tears for them. Regardless of the goals I have with my business, it‚Äôs all rooted in touching as many lives as I can, so that other women are able to become the best version of themself they never dreamed possible.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
To learn our entire team helped 1,300 people open up the opportunity to change their life gives me chills.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
And it reminds me how many people are STILL out there, struggling with all of that. For every woman who is giddy for the first time in a bathing suit, there‚Äôs another crying at the thought of wearing one. For every girl surpassing her goals, there‚Äôs another who doesn‚Äôt think she even deserves to feel success.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
That‚Äôs what fuels me to keep leading and encouraging others. Just think ‚Äî if that many people were given a chance to feel their absolute healthiest and happiest, and reclaim control of their life ‚Äî and it finally CLICKED ‚Äî just how different so many lives would be.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
This is so much bigger than me - yet I feel the power of that on such a close level.‚†Ä
‚†Ä
I invite you to listen in on our webinar this Sunday and hear more of what I do behind the scenes as a wellness coach, and the value it could have for you too. DM for the link to listen in!

description:
There's still a couple of you that's not sure how Matched Betting work and what it is. If you're one of those, make sure to read this.
'
There's 3 Matched Betting key terminologies you need to know about, that is bonus bet, cover bet and a lay bets.
'
Bonus bet: Well, the name says it all. Bonus bet is the free bet that bookmakers offer to attract new customers. '
Cover bet: The cover bet is the bet you place to ensure profit even though your bonus bet lose. Let's say Manchester United play against Tottenham at home, and your bonus bet is a Manchester United win, then your cover bet should be a Draw/away bet. That way you've covered every possibility. '

Lay bet: It is possible to place a lay bet instead og a cover bet. A lay bet is basically to play on something not to happen, in the same example as above that would mean to play on Manchester United NOT to win. That means you will act as the bookmaker, and that's only possible to do with betting exchanges. '

Hope this cleared things up, if not, send us a chat and we will answer all your questions üôÇ '

description:
Sales objection is an indication that the buyer is engaged, which sure beats apathy.

When a buyer indicates that he is not ready to buy, don't get discouraged. Use the following 4 steps to overcome sales objections and move closer to the sale.

1..Listen Fully to the Objection
Your first reaction when you hear an objection may be to jump right in and respond immediately. Resist this temptation. When you react too quickly, you risk making assumptions about the objection. Take the time to listen to the objection fully.

2..Understand the Objection Completely
Many objections hide underlying issues that the buyer can't or isn't ready to articulate. Often the true issue isn't what the buyer first tells you. It's your job to get to the heart of the objection, and then fully understand it and its true source.

3..Respond Properly
After you're confident you've uncovered all objections, address the most important objection first. Once you work through the greatest barrier to moving forward, other concerns may no longer matter or feel as important to the buyer.

4..Confirm You've Satisfied the Objection
Once you've responded to the buyer's objections, check if you've satisfied all of their concerns. Just because they nodded during your response doesn't mean they agreed with everything you said. Ask if the buyer is happy with your solution and explain your solution further if necessary. Some objections require a process to overcome, not just a quick answer.

Do you find this useful, share your experience on SALES OBJECTION. Tag a business owner,salesperson and a friend. Don't forget to like.

10 hard gut wrenching truths no one tells you about becoming an online entrepreneur...‚Å£
‚Å£
1. You can go from feeling like you‚Äôre a total badass, to feeling like you‚Äôre the biggest loser in the world in a matter of seconds... and go through that cycle multiple times a  day ü§™‚Å£
‚Å£
2. People closest to you will project their fears about your business onto you... don‚Äôt let that get in your head.‚Å£
‚Å£
3. Even though you‚Äôre an ‚Äúonline entrepreneur‚Äù there is so much work and connecting that can/should be done offline.‚Å£
‚Å£
4. Just because you‚Äôre educated and qualified in something, doesn‚Äôt mean people will buy from you. They need to know, like and trust you.‚Å£
‚Å£
5. You could spend months on a program/product, and want to destroy it all the next dayüôÉ‚Å£
‚Å£
6. Finding out what your niche is and who you‚Äôre taking too, is a lot harder than you would imagine... if you know, you know lol‚Å£
‚Å£
7. You can launch a program/product that you believe is amazing and no one will buy it. ‚Å£
‚Å£
8. You will correlate the success of your business with your personal worth... don‚Äôt do that, you‚Äôre two different entities. The sooner you can detach from your business as a part of who you are, the better. ‚Å£
‚Å£
9. Going online is not a get rich quick plan... you actually need a lot of patience and a lot of consistency to start seeing any kind of momentum.‚Å£
‚Å£
10. You want to grow and level up in life? Become an entrepreneur. It‚Äôs the FASTEST way to personal growth along with relationships.‚Å£
‚Å£
*BONUS* ‚Å£
Everyone has, or is currently dealing with these things. No one is immune from it, despite what you see and hear from people you look up too. ‚Å£
‚Å£
All of this being said, you still have a drive and a want to keep pushing through, until you do start seeing that success.‚Å£
‚Å£
In my eyes, that‚Äôs what makes you a successful entrepreneur.‚Å£
‚Å£
Ps. I felt like this picture was fitting considering it‚Äôs May and it‚Äôs been snowing over the past 3 days... love that for us üôÉüòÇ‚Å£

description:
friends, please remove ‚ÄúI should‚Äù from your daily vocabulary. part 1/3

see if this story sounds familiar to anyone. when I graduated college, I made a list of requirements for my dream job. it looked something like this:
‚Ä¢ responsible for my own time.
‚Ä¢ freedom to work remotely.
‚Ä¢ not working in an office / spending the day outside of a cubicle.
‚Ä¢ having control over my own schedule, days off, time off, or being able to take into consideration the times of day I worked best (I‚Äôve always worked better in the morning).
‚Ä¢ doing something that makes me happy, helps me give back, and doesn‚Äôt fill me with dread and anxiety.

but I was told not to expect that would happen. so I worked from 2010-2016 in sports marketing, sales, and client services. I learned a ton. I grew into a great leader and coach. I managed six and seven figure accounts, created strategic marketing campaigns, sold more playoff tickets in a day than anyone else on staff did in a week.

but my job looked like this:
‚Ä¢ working in an office.
‚Ä¢ not able to work remotely.
‚Ä¢ being micro-managed.
‚Ä¢ not having control over my time.
‚Ä¢ being unhappy.

and I was doing it all for other people. I was doing what people told me I SHOULD do, during my early years of work.

it took me 6 years before I paused to consider if there was another way.

what does your dream job look like? something you ‚Äúshould‚Äù do or something you want to do?
